DB Development Life Cycle :- 
----------------------------------------

Analysis
Design
Develop
Test
Deploy
Maintain
 
DB Design :-
-----------------

  => Designing DB means designing tables
  => DB is designed by DB Designers / Architects
  => DB is designed by using

          1   ER Model  (Entity Relationship)
          2   Normalization

Development :- 
---------------------

  => DB is developed by DB Developers & DBAs (DB Administrator)
  => DB is developed by using any rdbms tools like ORACLE.

                  Developer			DBA
	
	  creating tables			installation of oracle
	  creating views			creating database
	  creating synonyms			creating userids
	  creating sequences		db backup & restore
	  creating indexes			db export & import
	  creating procedures		performance tuning
	  creating functions
	  creating triggers
	  writing queries

  Test :- 
  -----------

   => DB is tested by QA (Quality Assurance) team by  

               1   manually
               2   automatically (using selenium)
 
  Deployment :-
   ------------------
 
 => Deployment means moving db from dev server  to prod server
 => once db is deployed then end user can use db for day-to-day transactions
 
