  versions of oracle :- 
  ----------------------------
  
    2,3,4,5,6,7,8i,9i,10g,11g,12c,18c,19c,21c,23ai,26ai

 		i    =>   internet
	                g   =>   grid
                                 c   =>   cloud
                                 ai  =>  artificial intelligence

  => before 8 oracle supports only desktop application and 8 onwards
       oracle supports web applications.

  => grid means collection of server ,  from ver 10  onwards oracle db can be
       accessed through multiple servers and the advantage of grid is it improves
       availability

 => from 12c onwards oracle db can be deployed 

         1 on premises
         2 on cloud

  => in  " on  premises "  db is deployed in the server managed by client

  =>  in  "  on cloud " db is deployed in the server managed by cloud service provide
        for ex amazon.
